<p>The <code>slashes</code> function adds backslashes before special characters.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'It is a "test"' | slashes{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'It is a "test"' | slashes}</b></p>

<h2>Escape Quotes</h2>
<pre>{open}echo "He said 'hello'" | slashes{close}</pre>
<p>Escaped: <b>{echo "He said 'hello'" | slashes}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Name: "John"' | slashes | left(20){close}</pre>
<p>Truncated: <b>{echo 'Name: "John"' | slashes | left(20)}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Use <code>slashes</code> when you need to escape strings for contexts requiring backslash escaping.</p>
